  "prompt": "Did any of Melania Trump's family come to her wedding? Did anyone \"give her away?\" And who paid for her wedding gown?",
  "response": "Yes, several members of Melania Trump's family attended her wedding to Donald Trump on January 22, 2005. Her parents, **Andrej and Jacqueline Knavs**, accompanied her on the special day, along with her brother, **Damijan Knavs**. Unfortunately, her sister was unable to attend due to illness and watched the ceremony from overseas.\n\nRegarding the traditional role of \"giving away\" the bride, Melania's father, **Andrej Knavs**, took on this honor and walked her down the aisle during the ceremony.\n\nAs for her wedding gown, Melania wore a custom-designed dress that was reportedly paid for by her family. The elegant gown reflected her personal style and the significance of the occasion, ensuring that her wedding attire was both memorable and sophisticated.\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Family Attendance:** Both of Melania Trump\u2019s parents and her brother attended her wedding.\n- **Who Gave Her Away:** Her father, Andrej Knavs, gave her away.\n- **Wedding Gown Payment:** Her family paid for her custom-designed wedding dress.",
